text: I smile
column4: wave

column6: I don't know if he made it out of the U92 restroom alive.

text: So
column4: faced with the certain horror of Ralph F'ing Nader judging me and/or contemplating my role in his hell
column5: I do exactly what you'd expect.

text: Do I tell him the toilet is messed up? Will he think it was my fault? Will Ralph Nader deem his bathroom visit unsafe at any speed?
Hello there, he says
column4: smiling. "After you
column6:
I motion to him. And in this moment, I have a dilemma.
881682099589271600,Mon Jul 03 01:12:48 +0000 2017,Finally I conquer it, wash my hands, and step outside. Ralph Nader is standing there, alone. He has just finished speaking.
881681879820382200,Mon Jul 03 01:11:55 +0000 2017,At the end of my shift, I had to use it. It was clogged (not my fault, trust). Nearly flooded it. Plunger, multiple flushes, all that.
881681151101984800,Mon Jul 03 01:09:01 +0000 2017,In that hallway was the entrance to a single toilet. This was the station bathroom. I was DJing on one end as Nader spoke on the other.
881680219815497700,Mon Jul 03 01:05:19 +0000 2017,Ralph Nader spoke at WVU about 10 years ago. I was a college radio DJ then. The station and an auditorium were connected by a hallway.
881679475976613900,Mon Jul 03 01:02:22 +0000 2017,Oh, did I ever. And I had blocked it out until this moment.
881679401217347600,Mon Jul 03 01:02:04 +0000 2017,Tonight, my mom texted me to let me know that my dad's friend got a real kick out of my Ralph Nader story. Me: I have a Ralph Nader story?"
